          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What is accrual vs cash accounting?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Accrual accounting records revenue when it is earned and expenses when they are incurred, while cash accounting records both only when money moves. Invoice a client Rs 1,00,000 on 28 March and receive payment on 10 May: accrual books the income in the year ended 31 March, cash books it in the next year. Companies in India must use accrual."
